classes.label: SetMap
description: A class for collecting items (V) based on some key (K)

children.label: has
description: Is there a group for the `key`?

children.label: add
description:
Add a value to the group with `key`, if the group doesn't exist
yet it is created.

children.label: get
description:
Get the group for the `key`, if the group doesn't exist then
`undefined` is returned.

children.label: values
description: Returns an iterator for the [K, V] entries stored in the SetMap

classes.label: TestLog
description: Logger which collects messages in memory for testing

functions.label: describeNode
description: Turn a Node instance into a string which describes the type, name, filename, and position of the node

functions.label: describeSymbol
description:
Get a human readable string describing a symbol, requires that symbols have a declaration
which will be passed to describeNode()

functions.label: getKindName
description:
Get a human readable name of the syntax "kind". TS nodes use enums for their "kind" field
which makes it tricky to know what you're looking at, and the `ts.SyntaxKind` map is lossy
because many enum members have the same numeric value. To get around this we convert the
ts.SyntaxKind map into a `SetMap` which puts all the syntax kind names for a given number
into a set and allows us to report all possible type names from `getKindName()`

functions.label: hasIdentifierName
description: Does this AST node have a name which is an identifier?

functions.label: isAliasSymbol
description: Is this symbol pointing to another symbol?

functions.label: isSystemError
description: Is this error instance a Node.js system error which has an error code attached?

functions.label: parseJson
description: Parse JSON, but thrown a more meaningful error message when parsing fails

functions.label: toError
description: Convert an unknown thrown value to an Error instance if it isn't alread

functions.label: tryReadFile
description:
Read a file, if the file doesn't exist return undefined. If any other
error occurs they will be thrown.

functions.label: tryReadFile
description:
Read a file, if the file doesn't exist return undefined. If any other
error occurs they will be thrown.
signature: (path: string, encoding: BufferEncoding | undefined) => Promise<string | Buffer | undefined>

children.label: step
description:
Write a message to the log indicating the beginning of a step, then run the passed
block, any log output produced inside that step will be indented and at the end the
duration of the step will be written. If the log level is below verbose then any
"verbose steps" executed inside this step will be summaried by this step at the end
as well.

children.label: name
description: a common name for steps of a specific type

children.label: desc
description: a specific name to describe the unique information about this step

children.label: block
description: the function body which defines this step

children.label: verboseStep
description:
Just like step(), except that unless the logging level is set to verbose the steps with
the same name will be summaried at the end of the containing step, rather than logged
directly.
